From 312911a541b48708c5d5a02a68df6d286589f89d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Renato Bardi <renato.bardi@live.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 07:27:30 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] fix(audit): eliminate duplicate events across the full
 pipeline
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root causes found and fixed:

P0 — event_id in audit_log() (_lib.sh)
Generate a unique <epoch_ms>-<hook>-<rand4hex> identifier on every
audit_log() call. Enables deduplication at every downstream layer.

P1 — flow-dispatcher / standalone hook double-logging
When flows.enabled=true, the same guard hook fired twice: once inside
flow_run_step() and once as an independent settings.json hook.
Fix: flow-dispatcher exports HAPAI_FLOW_EXECUTOR=1 before each step.
Guard hooks call _is_flow_managed() after read_input and exit 0
silently when running standalone while flows are active.

P2 — full-file sync re-inserting all rows on every run (bin/hapai)
hapai sync now tracks a cursor in ~/.hapai/state/sync_cursor (line
count of last successful upload). Each run uploads only new lines as
a delta file. GCS path includes the cursor offset so re-running sync
twice on the same day is idempotent.

P3 — no dedup at BigQuery ingest (infra/gcp/functions/main.py)
- Added event_id and reason fields to the BigQuery schema.
- Ingest uses MERGE WHEN NOT MATCHED INSERT keyed on event_id so
  rows already in the table are silently skipped.
- Batch-level dedup in Python deduplicates within the uploaded file.
- Legacy rows without event_id fall back to streaming insert.

P4 — COUNT(*) queries counting duplicate rows (main.py)
All dashboard queries now use a _dedup_cte() WITH clause using
ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY event_id) so any duplicate rows in
BigQuery are excluded before COUNT(). Handles legacy rows without
event_id via COALESCE fallback.

Tests: 134/135 pass. The 1 pre-existing failure requires claude CLI.
